You are analyzing code for **Path Traversal** vulnerabilities.

## What Is Path Traversal?

Path traversal (directory traversal) occurs when an application uses user-supplied input to construct file paths without proper sanitization, allowing an attacker to access files outside the intended directory. By injecting sequences like `../` or absolute paths, the attacker can read sensitive files (`/etc/passwd`, `.env`, source code) or write to arbitrary locations.

